:"Luke.19.5","text":"And when Jesus came to the place, he looked up, and saw him, and said unto him, Zacchaeus, make haste, and come down; for to day I must abide at thy house.","year":33},{"id":"reccfWaJ4afhkH2kw","ref":"Luke.19.6","text":"And he made haste, and came down, and received him joyfully.","year":33},{"id":"recRPQY7i3z1JRj6y","ref":"Luke.19.7","text":"And when they saw it, they all murmured, saying, That he was gone to be guest with a man that is a sinner.","year":33},{"id":"recPnfLQdERx9enwJ","ref":"Luke.19.8","text":"And Zacchaeus stood, and said unto the Lord; Behold, Lord, the half of my goods I give to the poor; and if I have taken any thing from any man by false accusation, I restore him fourfold.","year":33}]}
